# Dawn
  `ending := "dawn"`
  > Morning arrives all at once. Rain lifts from Brindlewick as if someone has drawn back a curtain.
  > In the village square, every bell rope trembles though no bell is visible.
  > `pool_offering` Somewhere nearby, a stranger laughs and flips a coin into the fountain.
  + Visit the changed village -> [.Aftermath]
  + Begin the test drive again -> [Start]("/main.saga")

## Aftermath
  > The woman with the blue scarf waits beside the dry fountain.
  + Ask what happened -> [.Explanation]
  + Leave Brindlewick by the north road -> [Epilogue]

### Explanation
  > "You woke what was buried," she says. "That is not the same as saving it. But sometimes it is enough."
  + Continue -> [Dawn.Aftermath]

# Return
  `ending := "return"`
  > You wake at the table in the Hollow Bell inn. Rain taps against the shutters.
  > The letter is gone, but your palm is black with old key oil.
  + Check what remains -> [.Inventory]
  + Begin again -> [Start]("/main.saga")

## Inventory
  > You remember fragments: a tower, a pool, the shape of a bell inside an eye.
  + `saw_hidden_name` Whisper the hidden name -> [Epilogue]
  + Go back to sleep -> [Start]("/main.saga")

# Epilogue
  > Brindlewick falls behind you. Somewhere under the road, something vast and hollow rings once.
  > `has_cloak` Your cloak snaps in the morning wind like a small, stubborn banner.
  + Start over -> [Start]("/main.saga")
